# Approach a person/object seen by vision: the target point may be stamped in
# any TF frame (base_link, a camera frame, map). nav_central transforms it to
# the map frame, picks the nearest COSTMAP-FREE pose `standoff` meters from the
# target (biased toward the robot's side, facing the target) and navigates
# there through the standard goal pipeline.
geometry_msgs/PointStamped target
float32 standoff        # meters from the target; <= 0 uses the default (0.65)
---
bool success
string error
geometry_msgs/PoseStamped goal   # the approach pose actually used
